<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/425> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #425" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.47.7; Diod. 13.7.1; Fast. Cap. (note 1); Chr. 354; Degrassi 26f., 97, 376f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/423> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #423" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "{Gr} ({Gr}), Diod.; Sp. Rutilius Crassus, Livy. Though plebeians appear as Military Tribunes before 400, when Livy notes the first one, no Rutilii appear in the Fasti for 250 years, nor do they use either the praenomen Sp. or the cognomen Crassus. It is probable that Diod. preserves the correct nomen. He may be a son of the Decemvir of 451. The confusion of names may possibly have arisen from the nearness of Rutulus, the cognomen of Nautius, Mil. Tr. c. p. 416." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/422> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #422" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Fast. Cap. is preserved P. Lucretius Hosti f. [- - - - -], Agripp. Menenius T. f. A. [- - - - -]; and Chr. 354 has Tricipitino et Structo III. Servilius has the praenomen Gaius in Diod., but L. (for C. ?) in Livy, the cognomen Structus and the office for the second time (Livy). See 427, note 1, and 419, note 1; and Degrassi 96f., on 419." .
